I've watched you for a long time because of your moderate take on things, but this was a poor call on your part. That was pure intolerance and I think you need to give your head a shake. You don't like the guys beliefs so you tell him to STFU and call him a "fuckface"? He has his beliefs and he's entitled to them and you're entitled to yours, but the idea of cultural diversity is to allow room for these beliefs with respect.


You don't have to like his beliefs, and you can disagree with them, but you don't have the right to attack them.


That was disappointing, you were disappointing, I hope to see better in the future.


Edit: I know many of you aren't going to agree with what I've said here, but attacking opposing viewpoints is not how you unite a population that is already so divided. Accepting differences is what so many of you have been fighting for, so do it.

snippet.textDisplay: I’m really surprised Philip DeFranco would promote this data collection scam. I’ve gotten my news from him since 2015, but this makes me question his credibility. The company Community is not transparent. They claim to connect celebrities with fans, but it’s actually just a marketing company that is collecting then eventually selling phone numbers.  I recognize most sites/apps we sign up for reserve the right collect and sell data in their terms & service, however, influencers telling fans “text me! 🤪” when it’s actually automated messages and the goal is to collect data seems very disingenuous.  I know Philip DeFranco has a company to run and has to make money outside of YT. But he danced around what this company actually is... I feel bamboozled.
